        {
            "id": "intro_nested_conditionals",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Nested Conditionals",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 1
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Sometimes you need to check conditions inside other conditions. This is called **nesting** - putting one `if` statement inside another `if` statement."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "basic_nested_if",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "heading",
                    "content": "Basic Nested If",
                    "properties": {
                        "level": 2
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "A nested `if` is an `if` statement inside another `if` statement. The inner `if` only runs if the outer `if` condition is `True`."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "It’s like going through doors - you can only open the second one if you’ve passed the first."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "has_cookie = True\nhas_milk = True\n\nif has_cookie:\n    print(\"You have cookies!\")\n    if has_milk:\n        print(\"And milk too!\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "You have cookies!\nAnd milk too!"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "nested_with_else",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can also use `else` with nested `if` statements. The `else` belongs to the closest `if` statement."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "has_cookie = True\nhas_milk = False\n\nif has_cookie:\n    print(\"You have cookies!\")\n    if has_milk:\n        print(\"And milk too!\")\n    else:\n        print(\"But no milk!\")",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "You have cookies!\nBut no milk!"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "indentation_importance",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**Indentation is crucial.** With nested `if` statements, indentation shows which `if` statement each block belongs to. Each level of nesting needs more indentation."
                }
            ]
        },
